<plot>This is a history of the England's Ealing Film Studios, from its beginnings in 1902. It follows the studio's successes through the 1930's, World War II dramas, the well-known 'Ealing comedies' with 'Alec Guinness' (qv), and the BBC's television productions. At the end we see the resurrection of Ealing with the release of _Importance of Being Earnest, The (2002)_ (qv).</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?200619</url></doc>
